summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingThe derm-advanced Eye Lift: inspired by injectables the Estée Lauder Advanced Night Repair Eye Lift + Sculpt Eye Cream targets all 4 eye dimensions: undereyes, lids, crow's feet, inner corners. Visibly lifts and sculpts the entire eye area.

Visibly lifts, sculpts and remodels around the entire eye area. Inspired by popular injectables, Eye Lift cream targets both static and dynamic lines:Existing "static lines" look significantly reduced.In a remarkable breakthrough, eye area skin is strengthened to help deactivate the look of "dynamic lines" caused by facial movement. Not only do these momentary crinkles constantly age your appearance, but they can also become permanent creases over time.Instant Refreshment. Weightless, fluid-yet-creamy texture. Glides on without tugging delicate eye skin. This anti-aging eye cream leaves skin feeling wrapped and cushioned.Inject new life into the look of your eyes.For all ages and skin types.Key IngredientsPowered By Advanced Night Repair Serum actives and moreExclusive Night Peptide helps optimize skin's natural rhythm of renewal.2HA Volume Filler helps the Eye Lift cream micro-cushion against eye lines. reviews.headline: Wonderful product!
reviews.comments: I really enjoyed this product; very light feeling during application. Not overly runny or heavily scented product. Easily blended and absorbs well into my skin. I have not been using for the full 4 weeks to see the full effects from a sample size but so far so good. I received this product for free from Estee Lauder and topboxcircle for testing and review purposes.

reviews.headline: Estee Lauder is the best!!
reviews.comments: This eye cream is rich, and smooth. It doesn't leave a greasy feel to your skin. My eyes look great!!

reviews.headline: Light smooth texture, great results!
reviews.comments: I've been using Estée Lauder's Advanced Night Repair Eye Lift + Sculpt Eye Cream for 3 weeks, and I'm genuinely impressed. I noticed an immediate refreshing and lifting around eyes. After about 2½ weeks, the long-lasting results are clear—my eye area looks smoother and  firmer.  The cream feels luxurious and light, and I love the spatula applicator, making application easy yet precise.  Honestly, one of the best eye creams I've tried.  I received this product for free from Estée Lauder for testing and review purposes

faceoff_positive.comments: I did a 4-week trial of Estée Lauder: Advanced Night Repair: EyeLift + Sculpt. I received a sample size of the product for free from Estée Lauder for testing and review purposes. Due to the size of the free sample, I was not able to use it twice a day as suggested, but I did get the opportunity to try it once daily which I applied after my usual cleanse and moisturize before bed. I noticed within the four weeks trial, a relevant reduction in crow's feet and fine lines, and reduction in eye area skin sagginess and loss of creepiness on the eyelid area.It has little to no scent, and definitely no burning nor stinging sensation in my sensitive eye area. From the very first use and continued for 4 weeks, at no time did i experience any agitation to my eyes nor any adverse effects. I gave 4 stars not 5 because it did seem to have quite a watery texture and it didn't stretch very far ; it would have been a 5-star review if the texture was more luxurious and cushiony/velvety feeling. At the retail price-point listed, I don't think I found enough unique benefit from this product to set it apart from other types of eye creams to want to afford to purchase it after the free sample has been exhausted but I am thankful for the opportunity to be part of the free trial in exchange for my honest review. If you're a diehard Estée Lauder user/fan, or are looking for a luxury nighttime eye cream, I definitely recommend this product: especially since you can use it all around the entire eye area without having irritation or concerns about damaging the eye or the sensitive skin around it!
faceoff_positive.headline: Sensitive Eyes Approved Fine-Line Fighter

faceoff_negative.comments:
To preface, I am in my mid-thirties, and while I use eye cream every evening it is mainly for preventative reasons. I have a couple deep expression lines at the outer corners but that's it, and I have yet to see any change in these lines with any eye cream I've ever used. My eyelids are oily so I usually opt to use eye creams only at night, HOWEVER with this one, I also used it on mornings I didn't apply makeup (for the purpose of this review, I didn't wear eye makeup for five days in order to test it better). I was…whelmed? There is little to no fragrance, excellent slip, and my skin did feel moisturized after applying it. That hydration also seemed to last until I applied it again. On occasion I did have a mild burning sensation, however, which reminded me of those plumping lip glosses. Not sure why they decided to call it cooling, if that's the effect they were referencing. I don't think it worked any better than any other eye cream I've ever used, but again, I'm preventing wrinkles, not trying to soften existing ones (yet). YMMV.

I knocked off a star for the absolutely horrid packaging, though. I didn't mind receiving a mini to review, but if they end up selling it in this type of packaging, skip it and try to get a decant if you want to test it out before investing in a full size (it looks like that uses a pump bottle, which will not have the same issues). The lid has a little scoop on it, which is very cute but when attached to a square bottle—how exactly am I supposed to get the product out from the bottom or top corners?? You don't need a lot of this product for each application, so I'm sure that without cutting the bottle open (which, good luck, it's a thicker plastic) you'd be losing out on a ton of product, even after forgoing the scoop and just tipping the bottle upside down. 

I received this product for free from ESTEE LAUDER for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Worst (mini) packaging I've ever received
